li of Africa\n|-\n| 20\n| [[Hafs ibn al-Walid ibn Yusuf al-Hadrami]]\n| 741\n| 744\n| Resigned\n|-\n| 21\n| [[Hasan ibn Atahiya]]\n| 744\n| 744\n| Ran away after opposition by the ''Hafsiya''\n|-\n| 22\n| [[Hafs ibn al-Walid ibn Yusuf al-Hadrami]]\n| 744\n| 745\n| Installed by the ''Hfsiya'', surrendered to his successor without a fight\n|-\n| 23\n| [[al-Hawthala ibn Suhayl al-Bahili]]\n| 745\n| 749\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 24\n| [[Al-Mughira ibn Ubayd al-Fazari]]\n| 749\n| 749\n| Died\n|-\n| 25\n| [[Abd al-Malik ibn Marwan ibn Musa ibn Nusayr]]\n| 749\n| 749\n| Unseated by the [[Abbasids]]\n|}\n\n==Abbasid Caliphate era (750\u2013969)==\n''See [[Abbasid Caliphate]].''\n\n===Governors during the First Abbasid Period (750\u2013868)===\n\n{| width=90% class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- style=\"background:#cccccc\"\n|-\n! #\n! Governor\n! Start\n! End\n! Period\n! Governor Title\n! Fate\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Salih ibn Ali ibn Abdallah ibn al-Abbas]]\n| 750\n| 751\n| 1 year\n| Wali\n| Became the wali of [[Palestine (region)|Palestine]]\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Abu Awn Abd al-Malik ibn Yazid]]\n| 751\n| 753\n| 2 years\n| Wali\n| Ran away after an epidemic\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Salih ibn Ali ibn Abdallah ibn al-Abbas]]\n| 753\n| 755\n| 2 years\n| Wali\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Abu Awn Abd al-Malik ibn Yazid]]\n| 755\n| 758\n| 3 years\n| Wali\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Musa ibn Ka'b al-Tamimi]]\n| 758\n| 759\n| 1 year\n| Wali\n| Died\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Muhammad ibn al-Ash'ath al-Khuza'i]]\n| 759\n| 760\n| 1 year\n| Wali\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 7\n| [[Humayd ibn Qahtaba]]\n| 760\n| 762\n| 2 years\n| Wali\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Yazid ibn Hatim al-Muhallabi]]\n| 762\n| 769\n| 8 years\n| Wali\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 9\n| [[Abdallah ibn Abd al-Rahman ibn Mu'awiya ibn Hudayj al-Tujibi]]\n| 769\n| 772\n| 4 years\n| Wali\n| -\n|-\n| 10\n| [[Muhammad ibn Abd al-Rahman ibn Mu'awiya ibn Hudayj al-Tujibi]]\n| 772\n| 772\n| 8 months\n| Wali\n| Died\n|-\n| 11\n| [[Musa ibn Ali ibn Rabah al-Lakhmi]]\n| 772\n| 778\n|