 al-Rumi]]\n| 915\n| 919\n| 4 years\n| Died\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Takin al-Khazari|Takin al-Khassa Abu Mansur Takin ibn Abdallah al-Harbi al-Khazari]] (2nd time)\n| 920\n| 921\n| 1 year\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Abu'l-Hasan Hilal ibn Badr]]\n| 921\n| 923\n| 2 years\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Ahmad ibn Kayghalagh]]\n| 923\n| 924\n| 7 months\n| Unseated\n|-\n| 7\n| [[Takin al-Khazari|Takin al-Khassa Abu Mansur Takin ibn Abdallah al-Harbi al-Khazari]] (3rd time)\n| 924\n| 933\n| 9 years\n| Died\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Ahmad ibn Kayghalagh]] (2nd time)\n| 933\n| 935\n| 1 year\n| Unseated\n|-\n|}\n\n===Emirs of the Ikhshidid Dynasty (935\u2013969)===\n''See [[Ikhshidid dynasty|Ikshidid Dynasty]].''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#cccccc\"\n|-\n! #\n! colspan=2|Governor ([[Emir]])\n! Start\n! End\n! Period\n! Fate\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Muhammad ibn Tughj al-Ikhshid]]\n| <small>''No picture available''</small>\n| 935\n| 946\n| 11 years\n| Died\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Abu'l-Qasim Unujur ibn al-Ikhshid]]\n| <small>''No picture available''</small>\n| 946\n| 961\n| 15 years\n| Died\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Abu'l-Hasan Ali ibn al-Ikhshid]]\n| <small>''No picture available''</small>\n| 961\n| 966\n| 5 years\n| Died\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Abu al-Misk Kafur]]\n| <small>''No picture available''</small>\n| 966\n| 968\n| 2 years\n| Died\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Abu'l-Fawaris Ahmad ibn Ali]]\n| <small>''No picture available''</small>\n| 968\n| 969\n| 1 year\n| Deposed by the [[Fatimid conquest of Egypt|Fatimid conquest]]\n|}\n\n==Fatimid Caliphate (969\u20131171)==\n''See [[Fatimid Caliphate]].''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- style=\"background:#cccccc\"\n|-\n! #\n! Governor\n! Start\n! End\n! Title\n! Fate\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Jawhar al-Siqilli]]\n| 969\n| 973\n| Governor, following the [[Fatimid conquest of Egypt]]\n| -\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Al-Mu'izz li-Din Allah]]\n| 973\n| 975\n| Caliph\n| -\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Al-Aziz Billah]]\n| 975\n| 997\n| Caliph\n| -\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Al-Hakim bi-Amr Allah]]\n| 997\n| 1020\n| Caliph\n| Disa