asty|Burji Mamluks]] (1382\u20131517)===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- style=\"background:#cccccc\"\n|-\n! #\n! colspan=\"1\" | Name\n! Start\n! End\n! Title\n! Fate\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Barquq]]\n| 1382\n| 1399\n| Sultan\n| Died\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Faraj bin Barquq]]    ''1st reign''\n| 1399\n| 1405\n| Sultan\n| Escaped\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Izz ad-Din Abd al-Aziz|Abdul Aziz bin Barquq]]\n| colspan=\"2\" | 1405\n| Sultan\n| Died in custody\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Faraj bin Barquq]] ''2nd reign''\n| 1405\n| 1412\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned / Killed\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Al-Musta'in (Cairo)|Al-Adil Al-Musta'in Billah]]\n| colspan=\"2\" | 1412\n| Abbasid Caliph\n| Deposed\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Shaykh al-Mahmudi|Al-Mu'ayyad Shaykh al-Mahmudi]]\n| 1412\n| 1421\n| Sultan\n| Died\n|-\n| 7\n| [[Al-Muzaffar Ahmad|al-Muzafar Abu al-Saadat Ahmad]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\" | 1421\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Sayf ad-Din Tatar|Al-Zahir Sayf-ad-Din Tatar]]\n| Sultan\n| Died\n|-\n| 9\n| [[An-Nasir ad-Din Muhammad|as-Salih Nasir-ad-Din Muhammad]]\n| 1421\n| 1422\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 10\n| [[Barsbay]]\n| 1421\n| 1438\n| Sultan\n| Died\n|-\n| 11\n| [[Al-Aziz Jamal ad-Din Yusuf|Jamal ad-Din Yusuf]]\n| colspan=\"2\" | 1438\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 12\n| [[Sayf ad-Din Jaqmaq|Jaqmaq]]\n| 1438\n| 1453\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 13\n| [[Fakhr-ad-Din Uthman]]\n| colspan=\"2\" | 1453\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 14\n| [[Sayf ad-Din Inal|Inal]]\n| 1453\n| 1460\n| Sultan\n| Resigned due to illness and died\n|-\n| 15\n| [[Al-Mu'ayyad Shihab al-Din Ahmad|al-Mu'aid Shihab ud-Din Ahmed]]\n| 1460\n| 1461\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 16\n| [[Sayf ad-Din Khushqadam|Khushqadam]]\n| 1461\n| 1467\n| Sultan\n| Died\n|-\n| 17\n| [[Sayf ad-Din Bilbay|Bilbay]]\n| 1467\n| 1467\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned and died in custody\n|-\n| 18\n| [[Timurbugha]]\n| 1467\n| 1468\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 19\n| al-Ashraf [[Qaitbay]]\n| 1468\n| 1496\n| Sultan\n| Abdicated to his son\n|-\n| 20\n| [[An-Nasir Muhammad ibn Qaitbay|al-Nasir Abu al-Sa'adat Muhammad]] ''1st reign''\n| 1496\n| 1497\n| Sultan\n| Deposed\n|-\n| 21\n| {{ill|Qansuh Khumsama'ah|arz|\u0642\u0627\u0646\u0635\u0648\u0647 \u062e\u0645\u0633\u0645\u0626\u0647}}\n| colspan=\"2\" | 1497\n| Sultan\n| Escaped and disappeared\n|-\n| 20\n| [[An-Nasir Muhammad ibn Qaitbay|al-Nasir Abu al-Sa'adat Muhammad]] ''2nd reign''\n| 1497\n| 1498\n| Sultan\n| Assassinated\n|-\n| 22\n| [[Abu Sa'id Qansuh|az-Zahir Qansuh al-Ashrafi]]\n| 1498\n| 1500\n| Sultan\n| Abdicated\n|-\n| 23\n| [[al-Ashraf Janbalat]]\n| 1500\n| 1501\n| Sultan\n| Dethroned\n|-\n| 24\n| [[Tuman bay I]]\n| 1501\n| 1501\n| Sultan\n| Deposed and executed\n|-\n| 25\n| [[Al-Ashraf Qansuh al-Ghawri]]\n| 1501\n| 1516\n| Sultan\n| Killed in [[Battle of Marj Dabiq]]\n|-\n| 26\n| [[Tuman bay II]]\n| 1516\n| 1517\n| Sultan\n| Executed by the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] Sultan [[Selim I]]\n|}\n\n==Sources==\nBosworth, Clifford E., ''The New Islamic Dynasties:  A Chronological and Genealogical Manual'', Columbia University Press, New York, 1996 ([https://books.google.com/books?id=2O_BQs6Sro0C&printsec=frontcover&vq=mazyad&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q=mazyad&f=false Google Books])\n\n==See also==\n*[[History of Muslim Egypt]]\n\n[[Category:Heads of state of Egypt]]\n[[Category:Medieval Egypt|Governors]]\n[[Category:Lists of governors|Egypt, Islamic]]\n[[Category:Lists of rulers of Egypt|Islamic Egypt]]\n", "name_user": "Ro4444", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_rulers_of_Islamic_Egypt"}
{"title_page": "Edythe Elliott", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Edythe Elliott\n| birth_name         = Edythe Fletcher\n| birth_date         = July 14, 1886\n| birth_place        = San Francisco, California, USA\n| death_date         = April 9, 1978 (aged 91)\n| death_place        = San Diego, California, USA\n| occupation         = Actress\n| spouse             = Charles \"Royal\" Elliott\n}}\n'''Edythe Elliott''' (born '''Edythe Fletcher''') was an American [[character actress]] active primarily during the 1930s, 1940s, and 1950s.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yIShCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA28&lpg=PA28&dq=%22edythe+elliott%22&source=bl&ots=d0klGJfrK9&sig=ACfU3U2TM118rKVW2iuiebb5QeeT6_zDHg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjMkurrqrvkAhXaHzQIHSAuCQU4FBDoATADegQICRAB#v=onepage&q=%22edythe%20elliott%22&f=false|title=Wild Bill Elliott: A Complete Filmography|last=Blottner|first=Gene|date=2011-09-30|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780786469031|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cdnc.ucr.edu/?a=d&d=RBDN19160112.1.3&|title=Red Bluff Daily News 12 January 1916 \u2014 California Digital Newspaper Collection|website=cdnc.ucr.edu|access-date=2019-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nEdythe Elliott was born in [[San Francisco, California]] where her parents were involved in [[Vaudeville]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspapers.com/image/571967536/?terms=%22edythe+elliott%22|title=Vet of 60 Years in Theatre Has Forgotten to Grow Old|last=Russell|first=Kathlyn|date=19 Sep 1966|website=The Times-Advocate|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-09-06}}</ref> She developed a prominent career on the stage before moving to the screen. She married fellow actor Charles \"Royal\" Elliott in Oregon in 1906 in a ceremony performed before a large audience.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Selected filmography ==\n{{Div col}}\n*''[[Show Them No Mercy!]]'' (1935) - Mrs. Hansen\n*''[[I Married a Doctor]]'' (1936) - Mrs. Clark\n*''[[The Girl on the Front Page]]'' (1936) - Mrs. Stokes (uncredited)\n*''[[Stella Dallas (1937 film)|Stella Dallas]]'' (1937) - Department Store Clerk (uncredited)\n*''[[Crashing Hollywood (1938 film)|Crashing Hollywood]]'' (1938) - Barbara's Landlady (uncredited)\n*''[[Double Danger (1938 film)|Double Danger]]'' (1938) - Mrs. Edith Theron\n*''[[Condemned Women]]'' (1938) - Dr. Barnes (uncredited)\n*''[[Fixer Dugan]]'' (1939) - Mrs. Fletcher\n*''[[The Rookie Cop]]'' (1939) - Mrs. Maitland (uncredited)\n*''[[Bachelor Mother]]'' (1939) - Minor Role (uncredited)\n*''[[Dancing Co-Ed]]'' (1939) - Housemother Listening to Beethoven (uncredited)\n*''Beware Spooks!'' (1939) - Woman Radio Announcer (uncredited)\n*''[[Gone with the Wind (film)|Gone with the Wind]]'' (1939) - General's Wife (uncredited)\n*''[[Nobody's Children (1940 film)|Nobody's Children]]'' (1940) - Mrs. King (uncredited)\n*''[[Blondie in Society]]'' (1941) - Angry Neighbor Who Had a Birthday Cake (uncredited)\n*''[[The Medico of Painted Springs]]'' (1941) - Maw Blaine\n*''[[The Richest Man in Town]]'' (1941) - Elderly Woman (uncredited)\n*''[[The Iron Claw (1941 serial)|The Iron Claw]]'' (1941, Serial) - Milly Leach\n*''[[Father Takes a Wife]]'' (1941) - Mrs. Plant, at Wedding (uncredited)\n*''[[Harmon of Michigan]]'' (1941) - Mrs. Davis (uncredited)\n*''[[The Stork Pays Off]]'' (1941) - Mrs. Gadsby (uncredited)\n*''The Power of God'' (1942) - Mrs. Gilder\n*''[[The Man Who Returned to Life]]'' (1942) - Mrs. Turner (uncredited)\n*''[[Bullets for Bandits]]'' (1942) - Queen Katey\n*''[[Flight Lieutenant (film)|Flight Lieutenant]]'' (1942) - Mrs. Edythe Rhodes (uncredited)\n*''[[Blondie for Victory]]'' (1942) - Housewife of America (uncredited)\n*''[[Stand By All Networks]]'' (1942) - Mrs. Elliott (uncredited)\n*''[[Valley of Hunted Men]]'' (1942) - Elisabeth Schiller\n*''[[Lucky Jordan]]'' (1942) - 2nd Secretary (uncredited)\n*''[[Junior Army]]'' (1942) - Mrs. Pamela Fer