te Filmography|last=Blottner|first=Gene|date=2011-09-30|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780786469031|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cdnc.ucr.edu/?a=d&d=RBDN19160112.1.3&|title=Red Bluff Daily News 12 January 1916 \u2014 California Digital Newspaper Collection|website=cdnc.ucr.edu|access-date=2019-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nEdythe Elliott was born in [[San Francisco, California]] where her parents were involved in [[Vaudeville]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspapers.com/image/571967536/?terms=%22edythe+elliott%22|title=Vet of 60 Years in Theatre Has Forgotten to Grow Old|last=Russell|first=Kathlyn|date=19 Sep 1966|website=The Times-Advocate|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-09-06}}</ref> She developed a prominent career on the stage before moving to the screen. She married fellow actor Charles \"Royal\" Elliott in Oregon in 1906 in a ceremony performed before a large audience.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Selected filmography ==\n{{Div col}}\n*''[[Show Them No Mercy!]]'' (1935) - Mrs. Hansen\n*''[[I Married a Doctor]]'' (1936) - Mrs. Clark\n*''[[The Girl on the Front Page]]'' (1936) - Mrs. Stokes (uncredited)\n*''[[Stella Dallas (1937 film)|Stella Dallas]]'' (1937) - Department Store Clerk (uncredited)\n*''[[Crashing Hollywood (1938 film)|Crashing Hollywood]]'' (1938) - Barbara's Landlady (uncredited)\n*''[[Double Danger (1938 film)|Double Danger]]'' (1938) - Mrs. Edith Theron\n*''[[Condemned Women]]'' (1938) - Dr. Barnes (uncredited)\n*''[[Fixer Dugan]]'' (1939) - Mrs. Fletcher\n*''[[The Rookie Cop]]'' (1939) - Mrs. Maitland (uncredited)\n*''[[Bachelor Mother]]'' (1939) - Minor Role (uncredited)\n*''[[Dancing Co-Ed]]'' (1939) - Housemother Listening to Beethoven (uncredited)\n*''Beware Spooks!'' (1939) - Woman Radio Announcer (uncredited)\n*''[[Gone with the Wind (film)|Gone with the Wind]]'' (1939) - General's Wife (uncredited)\n*''[[Nobody's Children (1940 film)|Nobody's Children]]'' (1940) - Mrs. 